label: Miscellaneous - 17th, 18th, and 19th Centuries
description: Box 47 - Miscellaneous has four file folders that contain documents created between 1565 and 1821. The first folder is entitled, "6. Miscellaneous: 1614, 1788, 1835," which contains: a 1614 br√®ves (French, 2 folios), and a 1788 wedding announcement (Spanish, 1 folio). The second folder is entitled, "Alphabetical Indices - Baptisms (1st Book) St. Augustine," which contains: an index for Box 16 - Baptisms - 1784-1792 (Spanish, 4 folios), and an index for Box 17 - Baptisms - 1784-1792 (Spanish, 4 folios). The third folder is entitled, "2. Notarized Papers - Marriages, 1778-1785," which includes various documents (Spanish, 16 folios). The fourth folder is entitled, "Sacramental Register - Baptisms: 1791-1804," which includes an abridged baptismal register, arranged chronologically beginning in 4 February 1791 through 26 April 1804. These entries presumably appear in their full length in Boxes 16, 23, and 26 (Spanish, 12 folios).
